    <h1>Book char&#xAD;ac&#xAD;ter HIJINKS</h1>
    <h2>Dive into Sin&#xAD;ga&#xAD;pore&#x2019;s lat&#xAD;est mid&#xAD;dle-grade and young-adult reads, as The Sun&#xAD;day Times asks their au&#xAD;thors what their char&#xAD;ac&#xAD;ters would get up to in the hol&#xAD;i&#xAD;days</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201122/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-22"><time>2020-11-22</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Olivia Ho&#xD;&#xA;As&#xAD;sis&#xAD;tant Life Edi&#xAD;tor</span>
    </section>

    <p>MY BFF IS AN ALIEN #2: SAB­O­TAGE</p>
    <p>By Vi­vian Teo Epi­gram Books/ Pa­per­back/</p>
    <p>192 pages/ $13.80/ Avail­able at bit.ly/Sab­o­tage_Teo</p>
    <p>In My BFF Is An Alien, Abri­ana Yeo, 13, dis­cov­ered that her best friend Oc­tavia Wu was a refugee from an­other planet. Oc­tavia has since sur­vived in­ter­ga­lac­tic war and been re­united with Abri­ana at Bukit Timah Sec­ondary Girls’ School, but a vi­ral video of an en­counter be­tween them and a wild boar may ex­pose Oc­tavia’s se­cret alien iden­tity.</p>
    <p>“Abri­ana was re­ally based on the girl I was when I was 13, hav­ing started sec­ondary school unath­letic and quite friend­less,” says Teo, 42, who is in­ter­ested in ex­am­in­ing bul­ly­ing, so­cial me­dia use and gen­der stereo­types.</p>
    <p>Her daugh­ters are aged 10 and eight and she has bought at least 20 books to tide them over the hol­i­days.</p>
    <p>Q: How are Abri­ana and Oc­tavia spend­ing their school hol­i­days?</p>
    <p>As she hates sweat­ing un­der the sun, Abri­ana would en­joy some good books and binge-watch tele­vi­sion se­ries in the com­fort of air-con­di­tion­ing.</p>
    <p>But her na­ture-lov­ing and sporty BFF Oc­tavia would even­tu­ally guilt-trip her into cy­cling at East Coast Park and hik­ing at the Bukit Timah Na­ture Re­serve on the pre­text of get­ting fresh air and some ex­er­cise.</p>

